org.onyxplatform.api.java

Class Job

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.onyxplatform.api.java.Job
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OnyxNames

    public class Job
extends java.lang.Object
implements OnyxNames
    A job is the collection of a workflow, catalog, flow conditions, lifecycles, and execution parameters. A job is most coarse unit of work, and every task is associated with exactly one job - hence a peer can only be working at most one job at any given time.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Job

        public Job(TaskScheduler ts)
        Constructs a new Job object. Creating a new Job requires passing an existing TaskScheduler object. The new Job will be initialized with empty components, including associated Workflow, Catalog, Lifecycles, FlowConditions, Windows, and Triggers objects.
        Parameters:
        ts - taskScheduler object specifying running job conditions

      • Job

        public Job(Job j)
        Constructs a new Job object based on an existing Job object. This new Job will use the existing Job object components, including the existing TaskScheduler, Workflow, Catalog, Lifecycles, FlowConditions, Windows, and Triggers.
        Parameters:
        j - existing Job to use as a template for new Job
